.TH "traceFmt" "1" "" "SequoiaDB User Manuals" ""
.hy
.SH NAME
.PP
traceFmt \- Format trace input to output by type.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]traceFmt(<formatType>,<input>,<output>)\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
Global
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The trace file exported by db.traceOff() is in binary format and is not
convenient for users to read.
This command can be used to format the trace file into user\-readable content
and output it to the specified file.
.SH PARAMETERS
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]formatType\f[] ( \f[I]Int32\f[], \f[I]Required\f[] )
.PP
\f[C]formatType\f[] can take the following two values:
.IP \[bu] 2
0: Output analysis file, including thread execution sequence (output file suffix
is .flw), execution time analysis(output file suffix is .CSV), execution time
peak(output file suffix is .except) and trace record error information(output
file suffix is .error).
.IP \[bu] 2
1: Output dump record information(output file suffix is .fmt).
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.RE
.RS
.PP
The CSV file can be viewed by using Excel.
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]input\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[]， \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
The binary file that db.traceOff() exports
.RE
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[C]output\f[] ( \f[I]String\f[]， \f[I]Required\f[] )
.RS 2
.PP
Output target file
.RE
.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return void.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
the exceptions of \f[C]traceFmt()\f[] are as below:
.PP
